<div class="terms">
    <h1>Standard Terms &amp; Conditions of Sale</h1>
    <p class="terms__intro">
        Version {{ $application->terms_version }} &middot; Herocom Distribution (Pty) Ltd.
        These terms form part of every agreement and of the application signed overleaf.
    </p>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">1. INTERPRETATION AND DEFINITIONS</p>
        <p>Unless expressly stated otherwise, the following applies:</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">1.1</span> These Terms and Conditions of Sale ("Contract") govern all goods supplied by Herocom Distribution (Pty) Ltd ("Herocom Distribution"), whose registered office is located at 15 Desi Street, Industria, Middelburg, Mpumalanga, South Africa.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">1.2</span> The Standard Terms and Conditions form part of every agreement entered into between the parties and shall apply to all dealings between them.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">1.3</span> All agreements and these Standard Terms and Conditions are exclusively governed by, and interpreted in accordance with, the laws of the Republic of South Africa, except where the laws of another jurisdiction compulsorily apply. Nothing in this Contract shall be interpreted to limit any rights afforded under South African law, including the Consumer Protection Act (CPA). Where legislation grants additional or alternative rights, such rights shall be afforded to the relevant party, and both parties shall cooperate amicably to ensure such rights are upheld.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">1.4</span> Headings are included for convenience only and shall not affect interpretation.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">1.5</span> Expressions denoting:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Any gender (masculine, feminine, or neuter) includes reference to the others.</li>
            <li>The singular includes the plural, and vice versa.</li>
            <li>A natural person includes a juristic person, and vice versa.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">1.6</span> Where figures are expressed in both numerals and words, the wording shall prevail in the event of conflict.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">1.7</span> Notice periods shall be calculated by excluding the first day and including the last. If a notice period expires on a non-business day, it will be deemed to expire on the next business day.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">1.8</span> Words or expressions defined in any clause shall bear the same meaning throughout the agreement unless the context clearly indicates otherwise.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">1.9</span> The following rules of construction shall not apply:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Contra proferentem rule: the principle that an agreement is interpreted against the party who drafted it.</li>
            <li>Eiusdem generis rule: where specific words of a class are used with general words, the specific words shall not limit the scope of the general words. If a provision is followed by "including" and examples, such examples shall not restrict the general ambit of the provision.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">1.10</span> Any illustrations, drawings, price lists, specifications, dimensions, performance figures, or technical data provided by Herocom Distribution in connection with the agreement—whether written or not—are supplied for reference only. They do not form part of the agreement and must not be relied upon by the Buyer unless expressly warranted or guaranteed in writing by Herocom Distribution and expressly incorporated into the agreement.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">1.11</span> If any term, condition, requirement, or provision of this agreement is declared by a court of competent jurisdiction to be illegal, void, unenforceable, or contrary to public policy, such provision shall be deemed ineffective without impacting the validity or enforceability of the remainder of this agreement. It is the express intention of the parties that, had they known of such invalidity or unenforceability, they would nonetheless have entered into this agreement containing all the other terms and conditions herein.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">1.12</span> For purposes of this agreement, the following expressions shall bear the meanings set out below, and related expressions shall carry corresponding meanings:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Agreement:</strong> Refers collectively to the sale agreement between the parties, whether in the form of a CF Sale Agreement or COD Sale Agreement, together with the Standard Terms and Conditions and the Herocom Distribution Application Form.</li>
            <li><strong>Business Day:</strong> Any day other than a Saturday, Sunday, or public holiday in the Republic of South Africa.</li>
            <li><strong>Buyer:</strong> The natural or juristic person who has entered into a sale agreement with Herocom Distribution, under which goods are sold to such person, and whose details appear on the Herocom Distribution Application Form.</li>
            <li><strong>Calendar Month:</strong> A period of 30 or 31 days, forming part of the twelve named months of a year, commencing on the first day of the month and ending on the last day thereof.</li>
            <li><strong>CF Sale Agreement:</strong> A sale agreement concluded between Herocom Distribution and the Buyer, under which the Buyer purchases goods using a pre-approved credit facility backed by Credit Guarantee, subject to the standard terms and conditions of sale.</li>
            <li><strong>CPA:</strong> The Consumer Protection Act, 68 of 2008, as amended from time to time, together with its regulations.</li>
            <li><strong>COD Sale Agreement:</strong> A sale agreement concluded between Herocom Distribution and the Buyer, under which the purchase price must be paid via Electronic Fund Transfer (EFT) upon placing the order, subject to the standard terms and conditions of sale.</li>
            <li><strong>Credit Expiry Date:</strong> The date on which the agreed credit period under a CF Sale Agreement ends, at which point the full outstanding purchase price becomes due and payable to Herocom Distribution.</li>
            <li><strong>Credit Facility:</strong> A facility granted at the discretion of Herocom Distribution, enabling the Buyer to purchase goods with deferred payment terms. The Buyer has no entitlement to demand such facility.</li>
            <li><strong>Day:</strong> A calendar day, spanning from 00:00 to 24:00.</li>
            <li><strong>Delivery Address:</strong> The physical address designated by the Buyer for delivery of goods.</li>
            <li><strong>Delivery Date:</strong> The date scheduled for delivery of goods to the Buyer by Herocom Distribution.</li>
            <li><strong>Goods:</strong> Any items or products listed on Herocom Distribution's forms, price lists, quotations, sale orders, or tax invoices, supplied to the Buyer under this agreement.</li>
            <li><strong>Tax Invoice:</strong> The document issued by Herocom Distribution to the Buyer specifying the date by which payment must be made.</li>
            <li><strong>Normal Business Hours:</strong> The hours between 08:00 and 17:00 on Business Days during which Herocom Distribution operates.</li>
            <li><strong>Parties:</strong> Refers collectively to Herocom Distribution and the Buyer. "Party" refers to either of them individually.</li>
            <li><strong>Herocom Distribution:</strong> Herocom Distribution (Pty) Ltd, a private company incorporated in the Republic of South Africa, being the seller of goods under this agreement.</li>
            <li><strong>Herocom Distribution Application Form:</strong> The application form completed by the Buyer containing its details, which forms part of this agreement.</li>
            <li><strong>Standard Terms &amp; Conditions:</strong> The standard terms and conditions of sale as published on Herocom Distribution's website.</li>
            <li><strong>Year:</strong> A period of 365 consecutive days. For purposes of this agreement, leap years are disregarded.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">2. VARIATION AND AMENDMENTS</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">2.1</span> This agreement constitutes the full and complete understanding between Herocom Distribution and the Buyer, and incorporates all provisions agreed upon by the parties in relation to its subject matter.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">2.2</span> Herocom Distribution reserves the right to amend these standard terms and conditions from time to time, whether by addition, removal, or modification ("the amendment"). In the event of such amendment, Herocom Distribution shall notify the Buyer in writing via electronic mail, specifying the exact nature and content of the amendment.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">2.3</span> If the Buyer does not respond in writing via electronic mail within 30 days of receipt of the amendment to indicate non-acceptance, the amendment shall automatically become effective and binding upon expiry of that 30-day period.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">2.4</span> Should the Buyer expressly reject the amendment in writing via electronic mail, Herocom Distribution shall be entitled to cancel the existing agreement(s) between the parties by giving 30 days' written notice, also by electronic mail. If Herocom Distribution does not exercise this right of cancellation, the existing terms and conditions shall remain fully binding and unaffected by the amendment.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">2.5</span> Receipt of a delivery or read confirmation for the amendment notification (as referred to in clause 2.2) and/or cancellation notice (as referred to in clause 2.3) shall be deemed proof that the Buyer has received such notification. Except as provided in clauses 2.2 and 2.3 above, no variation, amendment, or consensual cancellation of this agreement or its terms shall be valid unless recorded in writing and signed by both the Buyer and a director or general manager of Herocom Distribution.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">2.6</span> No extension of time, waiver, relaxation, or suspension of any provision shall be binding unless similarly recorded in writing and signed by both parties. Any such extension, waiver, or relaxation shall not operate as an estoppel against either party, nor shall it prevent that party from subsequently enforcing its rights strictly in accordance with this agreement.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">2.7</span> Herocom Distribution shall not be bound by any representation, warranty, promise, or implied term not expressly recorded in this agreement, regardless of whether it induced the Contract. No person other than a duly authorized representative of Herocom Distribution has authority to amend, vary, delete, or accept any alternative conditions, or to agree to a consensual cancellation of this agreement.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">3. QUOTATIONS</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">3.1</span> Any quotation issued by Herocom Distribution to the Buyer shall not constitute an offer to sell goods, but rather an invitation to engage in business with Herocom Distribution. Such quotation may be withdrawn at any time by Herocom Distribution.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">3.2</span> Quotations remain valid for one (1) working day from the date of issue. They are prepared on the basis of prevailing exchange rates, freight charges, insurance, labour, material costs, and other applicable charges as at the date of issue. Any changes to these rates or charges after the one-day validity period shall entitle Herocom Distribution to adjust the quotation amount accordingly.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">3.3</span> A binding contract between Herocom Distribution and the Buyer shall only arise once Herocom Distribution has confirmed acceptance of the Buyer's order or quotation in writing, or upon the supply or tender of supply of the goods concerned to the Buyer.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">3.4</span> Herocom Distribution reserves the right to accept or reject, in whole or in part, any order placed by the Buyer pursuant to a quotation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">4. ORDERING OF GOODS</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">4.1</span> Herocom Distribution accepts both written orders (including those placed via the Website) and verbal orders. However, Herocom Distribution shall not be held liable for any errors or misunderstandings arising from a Customer's failure to submit a written order.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">4.2</span> Where orders are placed telephonically, Herocom Distribution may require the Buyer to confirm such orders in writing before acceptance. Herocom Distribution shall not be responsible for any errors or misunderstandings resulting from the Buyer's failure to record the order in writing.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">4.3</span> Orders placed by the Buyer shall constitute irrevocable offers to purchase the specified Goods at Herocom Distribution's prevailing prices as at the date of order, subject to clauses 3.2 and 3.3 above. Such orders may be accepted by Herocom Distribution through delivery of the Goods, written acceptance, or confirmation of the order.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">4.4</span> For Goods not held in stock ("Special Order Goods"), whether sourced locally or internationally, and for large quantity orders, the Customer shall be required to pay a deposit equal to 30% (thirty percent) of the estimated order value. Should the Customer cancel such an order after acceptance by Herocom Distribution, Herocom Distribution shall be entitled to levy a reasonable penalty fee in accordance with the Consumer Protection Act. The penalty fee shall be equivalent to the 30% deposit paid.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">5. PAYMENT OF GOODS ORDERED</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">5.1</span> The Buyer shall pay the amount reflected on the Herocom Distribution Tax Invoice or Sales Order, as applicable. Payment is due immediately upon placement of the order unless the Buyer has an approved credit facility with Herocom Distribution, in which case payment shall be made in accordance with the terms, conditions, and dates specified in the Buyer's credit facility agreement.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">5.2</span> Payment must be made via electronic funds transfer (EFT) directly into Herocom Distribution's designated bank account as specified on the Tax Invoice. Cash payments will not be accepted in-store.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">5.3</span> Herocom Distribution will issue a Tax Invoice to the Customer upon delivery of the Goods.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">5.4</span> The purchase price payable by the Buyer must be settled:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>In the currency stated on the Tax Invoice or Sales Order;</li>
            <li>Free of any deductions, bank charges, or other fees, and without any set-offs or withholdings.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">5.5</span> Although Herocom Distribution may approve the method of payment referred to in clause 5.2, all risk associated with that method of payment shall remain with the Buyer. Payment shall only be deemed complete once the full amount is received as freely available funds in Herocom Distribution's nominated bank account.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">5.6</span> Herocom Distribution does not accept payment by cheque.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">5.7</span> No discounts or extensions of time for payment shall be valid unless expressly agreed to in writing by a duly authorized representative of Herocom Distribution.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">6. OVERDUE PAYMENTS</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">6.1</span> If the Buyer fails to settle any amount invoiced by Herocom Distribution by the due date specified on the invoice or credit facility agreement, or fails to pay any other amount due and payable to Herocom Distribution under this agreement or otherwise, then—until such amount together with any applicable interest is paid in full—Herocom Distribution shall be entitled to exercise any or all of the following remedies:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Declare that all amounts owed by the Buyer to Herocom Distribution become immediately due and payable upon written notice to the Buyer; and/or</li>
            <li>Withhold delivery of any Goods sold but not yet delivered, with the Buyer remaining liable for all storage and related holding costs incurred; and/or</li>
            <li>Suspend or withhold performance of any obligations owed to the Buyer under this agreement or any other agreement between the parties; and/or</li>
            <li>Terminate, with immediate effect, any credit facilities previously approved or granted to the Buyer, whether under this agreement or otherwise; and/or</li>
            <li>Refer the Buyer to its attorneys for collection of the outstanding debt, with the Buyer liable for all legal costs incurred in connection with such collection; and/or</li>
            <li>List the Buyer as a defaulter with a credit bureau in accordance with Regulation 19(4) of the National Credit Act, 34 of 2005.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">7. CREDIT FACILITIES</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">7.1</span> Herocom Distribution will only consider credit applications submitted by Dealers.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">7.2</span> Unless the Buyer has applied for and been granted a credit facility by Herocom Distribution, all purchases of Goods shall be strictly on a cash-on-order (COD) basis.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">7.3</span> All credit facilities must be secured by a Credit Guarantee. The granting of any credit facility is entirely at the discretion of Herocom Distribution, and the Buyer shall have no entitlement to demand that such facilities be made available.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">7.4</span> Where a credit facility is approved, the nature, extent, and terms thereof shall remain at the sole discretion of Herocom Distribution. Herocom Distribution reserves the right to withdraw, increase, or reduce any credit facility at any time, without prior notice.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">7.5</span> Any credit facility granted shall be subject to the terms and conditions set out in the Buyer's Herocom Distribution credit facility application.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">7.6</span> If a Dealer's credit facility is withdrawn, the Dealer agrees that all subsequent purchases shall be made strictly on a COD basis.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">8. DELIVERY</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">8.1</span> Deliveries shall be made in accordance with Herocom Distribution's shipment policy, as follows:</p>
        <p class="subh">Johannesburg and Pretoria Deliveries:</p>
        <p class="sub">Orders delivered within Johannesburg and Pretoria will be made at Herocom Distribution's expense and at no charge to the Buyer, provided that the single order value is R2,500.00 (two thousand five hundred rand) excluding VAT, or more.</p>
        <p class="subh">Other Deliveries:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Herocom Distribution will appoint a third-party transporter to deliver the Goods, and the Buyer hereby authorizes Herocom Distribution to engage such third party on its behalf, on terms deemed appropriate by Herocom Distribution.</li>
            <li>To the extent permitted by law, the Buyer indemnifies Herocom Distribution against any claims arising from such third-party engagement.</li>
            <li>The Buyer shall be responsible for all delivery and/or shipment fees charged by the third party, which must be paid simultaneously with the purchase price of the Goods. Documentation evidencing such fees shall serve as prima facie proof thereof.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="subh">Partial Deliveries:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Where a credit facility has been approved, partial deliveries shall not affect the applicable payment period.</li>
            <li>Where no credit facility exists, the Buyer shall pay the full purchase price notwithstanding partial delivery.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="subh">Delivery Dates:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Herocom Distribution will notify the Buyer of the approximate delivery date ("Delivery Date"). Such date is an estimate only and shall not bind Herocom Distribution to deliver on or near that date.</li>
            <li>Any failure to deliver on the estimated date shall not entitle the Buyer to withhold, defer, or set off payment, nor give rise to a claim for damages.</li>
            <li>Notwithstanding the above, Herocom Distribution will take all reasonable steps to ensure delivery as per the communicated date.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="subh">Acceptance of Delivery:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>The Buyer shall accept delivery on the date tendered by Herocom Distribution and shall not be entitled to rescind the agreement, withhold or defer payment, or reduce the purchase price of the Goods delivered.</li>
            <li>Where delivery is made in consignments, Herocom Distribution shall not be obliged to deliver any further part of the order until payment for the portion already delivered has been made.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="subh">Buyer's Responsibilities:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>The Buyer shall be responsible for off-loading the Goods at the delivery address and must ensure that an authorized representative is present at handover. If no representative is present, the Buyer accepts responsibility for ensuring that delivery information is communicated to the person collecting the Goods on its behalf.</li>
            <li>The Buyer must inspect all Goods upon delivery and endorse the delivery note regarding any missing or damaged items. No claims will be valid unless the delivery note is endorsed and written notice is provided to Herocom Distribution within seven (7) working days of delivery, with full details. The Buyer bears the burden of proof for any missing or damaged Goods.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="subh">Failure to Accept Delivery:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>If delivery cannot be effected due to any act or omission by the Buyer, Herocom Distribution may charge storage fees and/or additional transport/shipping fees to complete delivery.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="subh">Split Deliveries:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Herocom Distribution may, with the Buyer's prior consent (which shall not be unreasonably withheld), split deliveries into quantities and dates as it deems appropriate.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="subh">Risk and Ownership:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Risk in the Goods passes to the Buyer upon collection from Herocom Distribution.</li>
            <li>If the Buyer elects to use a preferred courier, Herocom Distribution shall not be liable for any damage or loss once the Goods leave its premises. Risk passes to the Buyer upon handover to the courier, and a courier-signed invoice shall serve as proof of collection.</li>
            <li>The Buyer indemnifies Herocom Distribution against any claims arising from the use of the preferred courier, except where such claims result from gross negligence on the part of Herocom Distribution.</li>
            <li>Ownership of all Goods shall remain vested in Herocom Distribution until the full purchase price has been paid.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">9. RETURN OF GOODS</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">9.1</span> Unless otherwise stated herein and subject to applicable law, if upon inspection after delivery the Buyer discovers that the Goods supplied by Herocom Distribution are faulty or defective, the Buyer shall have seven (7) working days from the date of delivery to notify Herocom Distribution in writing. Such notification must specify the alleged defect in detail, be accompanied by the original Herocom Distribution invoice, and the Goods must be returned at the Buyer's expense, in their original packaging together with all manuals and additional parts.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">9.2</span> Failure by the Buyer to notify Herocom Distribution within the seven-day period shall release Herocom Distribution from any further obligation or liability in respect of the alleged defect. The Buyer shall provide Herocom Distribution with a reasonable opportunity to inspect the returned Goods and the alleged defect.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">9.3</span> Herocom Distribution will communicate its decision regarding the alleged defect to the Buyer, and such decision shall be binding. In any event, Herocom Distribution's liability shall be limited to refunding the purchase price of the Goods.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">9.4</span> Herocom Distribution shall be relieved of all obligations under this clause if:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Repairs or modifications have been carried out by anyone other than Herocom Distribution, unless expressly authorized in writing by Herocom Distribution;</li>
            <li>The Goods have been used with equipment, accessories, or parts not supplied or approved in writing by Herocom Distribution;</li>
            <li>The Goods have not been operated, maintained, or installed in accordance with Herocom Distribution's instructions, or have not been used under normal operating conditions.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">9.5</span> All Goods sold carry a one (1) year warranty against defects. The Customer must retain proof of purchase to verify the date of purchase. In terms of the Consumer Protection Act, this warranty may lapse if the Goods have been altered contrary to instructions or after leaving the control of Herocom Distribution.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">9.6</span> If Goods are returned within one year of purchase and proven defective by Herocom Distribution's supplier, Herocom Distribution may, at its discretion, replace, repair, or refund the Goods.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">9.7</span> Goods damaged due to power surges, blackouts, or lightning are expressly excluded from warranty coverage and will not be exchanged.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">10. BUYER'S IMPLIED WARRANTY ON GOODS SOLD BY HEROCOM DISTRIBUTION</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">10.1</span> The Buyer acknowledges that Herocom Distribution is not the manufacturer of the Goods sold under this agreement. As such, Herocom Distribution is not in a position to open sealed packaging to inspect the contents and therefore cannot warrant or guarantee that the Goods will:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Always be suitable for their intended purpose;</li>
            <li>Be free from defects or errors;</li>
            <li>Be of good quality or in proper working order;</li>
            <li>Be continuously available; or</li>
            <li>Be fit for any specific purpose.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">10.2</span> The Buyer further accepts that the Goods are supplied "as is" (voetstoots), as available and when available.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>All serialized products carry the original manufacturer's warranty, which Herocom Distribution will honor.</li>
            <li>All non-serialized products carry a limited warranty of seven (7) working days only.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">11. EXCLUSIONS AND LIMITATION OF LIABILITY</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">11.1</span> Herocom Distribution shall not be liable to the Buyer for any claims, losses, damages, costs (including attorney-and-client costs on a full indemnity basis), or any other liability (collectively referred to as "the claim") suffered or incurred by the Buyer, arising from or caused by Herocom Distribution acting on the Buyer's instructions in connection with any agreement ("the instructions"). The Buyer shall be responsible for all consequences resulting from any error, omission, discrepancy, or defect in such instructions.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">11.2</span> To the fullest extent permitted by law, the Buyer hereby waives any claim it may have or acquire against Herocom Distribution, its directors, officers, employees, contractors, or agents:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>For any indirect, incidental, consequential, or special damages (including loss of profit, loss of business, interruption of production or operations), arising from or in connection with any cause of action, whether contractual, delictual, strict, or statutory; and/or</li>
            <li>Arising from or in connection with any short delivery, defect in the Goods, or failure of the Goods to comply with the agreement, unless the Buyer notifies Herocom Distribution in writing within seven (7) working days of delivery, providing full details of the defect or failure.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">11.3</span> Herocom Distribution shall have no liability:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>For defects resulting from willful damage, negligence, fair wear and tear, abnormal working conditions, failure to follow Herocom Distribution's instructions (oral or written), improper use outside specifications, damage caused by improper maintenance, service or repair by untrained personnel, or unauthorized alterations or modifications;</li>
            <li>In respect of materials, equipment, or parts generally accepted in the industry to have a limited life expectancy, or those requiring replacement at specified service intervals ("consumable parts");</li>
            <li>Where spare parts or consumables not recommended or approved by Herocom Distribution are fitted, attached, or used with the Goods.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">11.4</span> Notwithstanding any other provision, the Buyer's claim against Herocom Distribution for direct damages, from any cause whatsoever, shall be limited to the purchase price of the Goods concerned.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">11.5</span> Herocom Distribution shall not be liable for any failure or delay in performing its obligations under the agreement where such failure or delay is caused by circumstances:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Beyond Herocom Distribution's reasonable control; or</li>
            <li>That could not reasonably have been foreseen before entering into the agreement; or</li>
            <li>That, having arisen, could not reasonably have been avoided or overcome.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">11.6</span> Such circumstances include, but are not limited to: strikes, lock-outs, shortages of labour or materials, transport delays, accidents, subcontractor or supplier defaults, riots, civil commotion, governmental actions, labour disputes, war, invasion, hostilities, terrorism, political or civil disturbances, adverse weather, or natural disasters such as earthquakes, floods, hurricanes, or droughts.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">11.7</span> Except where expressly agreed in writing and signed by both parties, the Buyer acknowledges and agrees that:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>The Goods are sold voetstoots (as they stand and where they stand), without any warranty or guarantee, whether express, implied, or arising under common law; and</li>
            <li>Herocom Distribution shall not be liable for any latent or patent defects in the Goods.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">11.8</span> The Buyer confirms that the provisions of this clause have been brought to its attention, that it had read and understood them, and agrees to be bound accordingly.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">11.9</span> Finally, Herocom Distribution shall have no obligation to defend, indemnify, or hold the Buyer harmless against any damages or costs arising from the infringement of patents, trademarks, or copyrights.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">12. JOINT AND SEVERAL LIABILITY</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">12.1</span> If this agreement is entered into between Herocom Distribution and two or more Buyers, such Buyers shall be jointly and severally liable for the full amount payable to Herocom Distribution under the terms of this agreement.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">13. TRANSFER (CESSION) OF RIGHTS AND OBLIGATIONS</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">13.1</span> The Buyer may not transfer its rights (cede), obligations (delegate), or both rights and obligations (assign) under this agreement without the prior written consent of Herocom Distribution, which must be obtained on each occasion.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">13.2</span> The Buyer further acknowledges and agrees that Herocom Distribution may, at its discretion, transfer its rights, obligations, or both under this agreement without providing prior notice to the Buyer.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">14. WITHOUT PREJUDICE</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">14.1</span> If the Buyer breaches this agreement, Herocom Distribution may, at its sole discretion, elect any remedy it deems appropriate, without limiting or prejudicing any other rights available to it under this agreement or applicable law.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">15. BREACH OF AGREEMENT AND TERMINATION</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">15.1</span> Herocom Distribution may terminate this agreement with immediate effect by providing written notice to the Buyer in any of the following circumstances:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>The Buyer fails to pay any amount due under this agreement by the specified due date and does not remedy such breach within five (5) days of receiving written notice from Herocom Distribution; or</li>
            <li>Where the Buyer is a natural person, he/she publishes a notice of voluntary surrender of estate, dies, or becomes subject to sequestration, curatorship, or proceedings resulting in the alienation or encumbrance of the whole or a substantial portion of assets; or</li>
            <li>Where the Buyer is a partnership, the partnership is dissolved; or</li>
            <li>Where the Buyer is a juristic person, it is wound up, liquidated, deregistered, placed under judicial management or business rescue (whether provisional or final, voluntary or compulsory), or passes a resolution to that effect; or compromises or attempts to compromise with creditors, defers or attempts to defer payment of debts, or alienates/encumbers the whole or a substantial portion of its assets; or</li>
            <li>The Buyer commits a material breach of any other provision of this agreement and fails to remedy such breach within five (5) days of receiving written notice from Herocom Distribution.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">15.2</span> In addition to the above, and without prejudice to any other rights Herocom Distribution may have, it may elect to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Declare all outstanding amounts, including those that would otherwise become due over the unexpired term of the agreement, as immediately due and payable, together with any arrears and applicable interest, and suspend performance of its obligations under this agreement or any other agreement with the Buyer until the breach is remedied; and/or</li>
            <li>Cancel this agreement and repossess any Goods sold; and/or</li>
            <li>Claim damages from the Buyer.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">15.3</span> Herocom Distribution shall not be obliged to perform any of its obligations under this agreement for as long as the Buyer remains indebted to Herocom Distribution in any amount, or fails to comply with any other obligations owed to Herocom Distribution, whether arising under this agreement or otherwise.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">15.4</span> Specifically, and without limiting the above, if delivery of an order is scheduled in stages, Herocom Distribution shall not be required to deliver any further part of the order until payment has been made for the portion already delivered.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">15.5</span> The Buyer agrees that the amount due and payable to Herocom Distribution may be determined and certified by a director or duly authorized representative of Herocom Distribution. Such a certificate shall be binding on the Buyer and serve as prima facie proof of the Buyer's indebtedness.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">16. COSTS INCURRED DUE TO BREACHING</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">16.1</span> The Buyer shall be liable for all legal costs incurred by Herocom Distribution as a result of any breach of this agreement, calculated on an attorney-and-own-client scale, together with any tracing fees and collection commission.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">16.2</span> The Buyer further indemnifies Herocom Distribution against any and all damages of whatever nature, however and by whomever caused, arising from the removal of Goods. This indemnity expressly includes, without limitation, the removal of repossessed Goods from the Buyer's premises or any other location where such Goods may be found.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">16.3</span> The Buyer agrees that Herocom Distribution shall not be required to furnish security in terms of the applicable rules of the Magistrate's Court or the High Court.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">17. JURISDICTION</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">17.1</span> In accordance with section 45 of the Magistrates' Court Act 32 of 1944, the parties consent to and submit to the jurisdiction of the Magistrates' Court for any proceedings arising from this agreement, regardless of whether the claim exceeds the monetary jurisdiction of the Magistrates' Court.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">17.2</span> Notwithstanding the above, Herocom Distribution retains the sole discretion to institute proceedings against the Buyer either in the Magistrates' Court or in any other court of competent jurisdiction, including any division of the High Court of South Africa.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="clause">
        <p class="h">18. NOTICES AND DOMICILIA</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">18.1</span> Unless otherwise specified, any notice given under this agreement must:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Be in writing to constitute a valid and effective notice;</li>
            <li>Be delivered by hand or sent via registered post to the party's physical address stated below, which address shall serve as the party's domicilium citandi et executandi for all purposes arising from or in connection with this agreement; or</li>
            <li>Be transmitted by telefax to the number provided by each party below.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">18.2</span> Delivery and receipt of written notices or documents:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Any written notice or document delivered by hand shall be deemed received by the addressee on the date of delivery.</li>
            <li>Any notice sent by registered post shall be deemed received on the tenth (10th) business day following the date of posting.</li>
            <li>Any notice transmitted by facsimile shall be deemed received on the first business day after the date of dispatch.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">18.3</span> Notwithstanding the above, any written notice or communication that has in fact been received by a party shall constitute sufficient notice, even if it was not delivered in the manner or to the address specified in this clause.</p>
        <p class="sub"><span class="n">18.4</span> Either party may change its physical address or telefax number, provided that such change shall only take effect once written notice of the new address or number has been received, or deemed received by the other party.</p>
    </div>
</div>
